# Privacy Policy — FIRE Planner

**Last updated:** April 6, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how **FIRE Planner** (“the App”), a financial independence and early retirement planning tool, handles information when you use the mobile application distributed on Google Play (and any other channels we may offer).

**Publisher:** Savia Labs, India.  
**Contact:** savialabs@gmail.com.

By using the App, you agree to this policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the App.

---

## 1. Summary

- The App is designed to work **primarily on your device**. Planning data, settings, and preferences you enter are stored **locally** using the device’s storage mechanisms (similar to app-specific storage / key–value storage).
- We **do not operate a user account system** in the App as described here, and we **do not intentionally collect or store your financial planning details on our servers** through the App in its current form.
- **Optional analytics consent** may be offered in the app; in the current build, analytics events are **not sent to external analytics providers** (they are not transmitted off the device for tracking).
- The App may request permission to show **local notifications** (reminders on your device only).
- The App may load **fonts** from **Google Fonts** when a network connection is available; that involves a request to Google’s servers (see Section 6).
- Opening links (for example to the **Google Play** store) is handled by your browser or the Play Store app and is subject to those services’ policies.

This summary is for convenience only; the sections below are controlling.

---

## 2. Information the App Processes on Your Device

Depending on how you use FIRE Planner, the App may process categories of information such as:

- **Planning and preference inputs** you provide (for example goals, assumptions, currency choices, and similar fields used for FIRE-style calculations and UI state).
- **App settings** such as onboarding completion, theme or display preferences, and stored choices related to features you enable.
- **Notification preferences** and scheduling data used only to schedule **local** reminders on your device.
- **Optional analytics consent flag** stored on the device to remember your choice.

We do not use this policy to ask you to list every field in the App; in general, treat anything you type or select in the App as information processed **on-device** unless we clearly state otherwise in a future update.

---

## 3. How We Use This Information

We use on-device information to:

- Provide core App functionality (planning views, calculations, and personalization you expect).
- Remember your settings between sessions.
- Schedule and manage **local notifications** when you opt in and the operating system grants permission.

We do **not** sell your personal information. We do not use your financial planning content for advertising profiling through this App in its current form.

---

## 4. Storage, Security, and Backups

- Data is stored **on your device** using platform APIs (for example Capacitor Preferences and related storage on web builds). Appropriate protection depends on your device passcode, OS security, and whether you allow device backups.
- **Device backup** (for example Android backup or cloud backup, if enabled) may include app data according to your device and manufacturer settings. We do not control those backups.
- **Uninstalling** the App typically removes app-specific data from the device; recovery may still be possible from backups until those expire or are deleted.

No method of storage or transmission over the internet is 100% secure; we encourage you to keep your device software updated and use a strong device lock.

---

## 5. Local Notifications

If you enable reminders, the App uses the operating system’s **local notification** APIs. Notifications are scheduled on your device. We do not need to send your planning content to our servers for those reminders to fire in the current design.

Notification permission is managed by your device settings (for example Android notification settings).

---

## 6. Third-Party Services and Network Activity

### Google Fonts

The App loads font files and stylesheets from **Google Fonts** (`fonts.googleapis.com` and related Google domains) when the UI is loaded and a network is available. Google may receive technical data typical of HTTP requests (such as IP address and user agent) as described in [Google’s privacy documentation](https://policies.google.com/privacy). Font requests may be cached by your device or browser after the first load.

### Google Play

If you use a link to rate the App or manage the App through **Google Play**, Google processes information under [Google Play’s terms and policies](https://policies.google.com/). We do not control Google’s data practices.

### Future analytics or crash reporting

If we add third-party **analytics**, **crash reporting**, or similar SDKs, we will update this Privacy Policy and, where required, obtain consent or provide opt-out in line with applicable law and store policies. The App may already store an **analytics consent** preference on your device for that purpose; until an external SDK is integrated, that preference does not result in personal data being sent to us for analytics.

---

## 7. Children’s Privacy

The App is not directed at children under 13 (or the minimum age required in your region). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided information through the App in a way that concerns you, contact us using the address above and we will take appropriate steps.

