## 8. Your Rights and Choices

Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict certain processing of personal data, and to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. Because most data stays on your device:

- You can often **delete** data by clearing app data or **uninstalling** the App.
- You can **withdraw notification permission** in system settings.
- You can change **analytics consent** where the App offers that control.

For rights that apply to us as a publisher (if any), contact us at the email address listed at the top of this policy.

---

## 9. International Users

If you use the App outside the country where the publisher is located, your information may be processed on your device and, when you use network features, by third parties (such as Google) in accordance with their policies and applicable law.

---

## 10. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the new version at the same URL (or notify you in-app or via the store listing where appropriate). The “Last updated” date at the top will change when we do. Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the updated policy, except where applicable law requires additional steps.

